the change to Nauruans in the creativeness of expressing their feelings. By using new means of communication like English, Internet communication has become possible. In the past 20 years, several Nauruans are scattered abroad either for education or employment. In this regard, the Internet allowed them to stay in regular contact with their families and friends regardless the distance.

Over the years, four people in the groups suggested the use of various media to enhance and update the contents of the Nauru Online Encyclopedia. It is because people no longer have the time to browse the Encyclopedia for information. These indicators call for the need of multimedia and multi-users’ features that could be presently found in the Online Encyclopedia.

Furthermore, one person in the group recommended the creation of an Nauru version of the Wikipedia. Though this person presented this recommendation as a commemorative gesture but it is in accordance with the proposed motive of producing one national resource as stated in the previous section.

Through these suggestions, it is obvious that the group believes that Nauruans need to be actively participating in the national development by using the Web as a platform or base for their input. In fact, using the is a way of communicating with Nauruans through the Web which could lead to better participation which is one of goals of using the Web.
